news.title: Motilal redevelopment on course as Bombay HC junks plea
news.para: The Bombay High Court has dismissed a review petition, clearing the path for the redevelopment of the 141-acre Motilal Nagar in Goregaon West, a project led by MHADA with Adani Realty as the consultant. This decision upholds MHADA's right to redevelop the land through private developers, rejecting the residents' group's claim for self-development.

news.title: Data for India's founder buys plot in Vasant Vihar for Rs 113 crore
news.para: Akhil Wable of DataforIndia acquired a 1,280-square yard plot in Vasant Vihar for Rs 113 crore from Eleannt Enterprises, who had purchased it earlier this year for Rs 95 crore. South Delhi's real estate market shows considerable appetite with limited inventory and high price appreciation, with transactions in Vasant Vihar reaching Rs 9–12 lakh per sq. yd.

news.title: EV charging points must for all new housing societies in Lucknow
news.para: Lucknow is set to boost electric vehicle adoption. New housing projects must reserve 20% parking for EVs. Lucknow Development Authority plans residential projects in Gomti Nagar, Aishbagh, and Basant Kunj. Designs will prioritize ventilation and larger spaces. Units will offer 2 and 3BHK options with amenities. Pricing will be below private sector rates.

news.title: Dumping of construction debris to invite stop-work notices in Kolkata
news.para: Kolkata Municipal Corporation will monitor dumping of construction materials. This action aims to prevent waterlogging across the city. Developers must store materials on the ground floor of buildings under construction. Failing to comply, KMC will issue stop-work notices. New Town Kolkata Development Authority will implement a redressal system for waste disposal. Building plans require a waste management plan for approval.

news.title: Madurai civic body cracks down on construction dust violations
news.para: Madurai Corporation is cracking down on construction sites, mandating green safety nets to control dust and debris due to rising complaints. Violators will face fines. A long-delayed project to establish a C&D waste processing plant remains stalled, hindering efforts to manage the city's 150 tonnes of daily construction waste.

news.title: Varanasi development body begins campaign on new building bylaws
news.para: The Varanasi Development Authority is actively promoting the UP Development Authority Building Construction and Development Bylaws-2025, aiming to streamline construction and encourage green buildings. Workshops are being conducted to educate builders and owners about the new regulations, including simplified zoning and relaxed standards for various establishments. The initiative also addresses concerns regarding road access requirements for new developments.

news.title: Thane civic body orders strict curbs on transport of construction material in Yeoor Hills
news.para: Thane Municipal Corporation has restricted construction material transport to Yeoor Hills. This is an environmentally sensitive zone. Permissions are needed from the Urban Development Department. Registration with the forest department is mandatory.

news.title: Jammu & Kashmir: 679 houses completed under PMAY in Bhaderwah
news.para: The Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) has achieved a milestone in Bhaderwah. The central government completed 679 houses. This initiative provides homes for underprivileged families. Many people lived in unsafe conditions. Now they have permanent homes with better facilities. Shahdi Lal, a daily wage labourer, received a new house. He thanked the government for the support.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh secures ₹12,031 crore under PMAY-Urban 2.0
news.para: Uttar Pradesh government received Rs 12,031 crore for housing. The money is for Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban) Mission 2.0. The goal is to provide permanent houses to the urban poor. Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath wants transparency and quality. Each house will be geo-tagged and photographed. Houses will resist disasters like earthquakes. Beneficiaries get Rs 2.

news.title: Over 18,000 tenants, servants verified in 15 days in Chandigarh
news.para: Chandigarh Police intensified security measures ahead of Independence Day by launching a 15-day verification drive for tenants and domestic helpers, scrutinizing over 18,497 individuals. Two employers were booked for negligence, and outstanding police officers were recognized for their efforts. SSP Kanwardeep Kaur urged residents to comply with verification protocols to maintain safety and prevent legal repercussions.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance records net profit of ₹62 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Sundaram Home Finance Ltd announced a slight dip in net profits, reporting Rs 62 crore for the April-June 2025 quarter, compared to Rs 66 crore last year. However, disbursements rose to Rs 1,488 crore from Rs 1,353 crore. The company's Assets Under Management (AUM) also saw a significant increase, reaching Rs 18,027 crore.

news.title: Bombay HC stays slum rehabilitation on Mumbai University land
news.para: The Bombay High Court has halted a Slum Rehabilitation Authority scheme on land acquired for Bombay University decades ago. The university claims the land, though acquired, wasn't properly mutated in records, leading to encroachment and a slum notification without their knowledge.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body to launch one-window building permission system from August 15
news.para: Kalyan-Dombivli Municipal Corporation (KDMC) is launching a pioneering one-window system for building permissions in Maharashtra, starting August 15. This initiative streamlines the application process by allowing online submissions to be routed to various departments, eliminating the need for multiple visits.

news.title: Goa government to legalise over one lakh houses existing prior to 1972
news.para: The Goa government has legalized over one lakh illegal houses built before 1972 through two circulars issued by the revenue department and the directorate of panchayat. These circulars, while not granting land ownership, legalize the structures and clarify land status, eliminating the need for a new bill in the assembly.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA recovers ₹1,410 crore for home buyers
news.para: UP-RERA has recovered ₹1,410 crore against 5,700 recovery certificates, with ₹861 crore recovered between August 2023 and July 15, 2025. Increased recoveries are attributed to monthly reviews with District Magistrates and pressure on defaulting promoters.

news.title: Odisha HC invalidates land transactions in Baniapat Khuntapada and Keonjhar
news.para: The Orissa High Court has nullified land deals involving ancestral property in Keonjhar due to the exclusion of rightful heirs and procedural irregularities. The court has directed an inquiry into the matter, implicating revenue officials and halting compensation disbursement by NHAI for a highway project.

news.title: Residents urge pollution board to regulate construction noise in Kolkata
news.para: Residents of a South Kolkata locality are urging the pollution control board to regulate noise from construction, similar to dust pollution control. They suggest sound suppression barriers and restricted timings. Constant high-decibel noise from jackhammers and piling is disrupting daily life.

news.title: Noida link among four Ghaziabad metro corridors in DMRC’s phase-V plan
news.para: The Delhi Metro Rail Corporation (DMRC) proposes extending the Blue Line from Noida Electronic City to Sahibabad, benefiting over 5 lakh residents.

news.title: Noida Metro's Aqua Line extension till Boraki multi-modal hub gets Centre’s nod
news.para: The Centre has approved extending Noida Metro's Aqua Line to Boraki, bringing it closer to Noida International Airport. This 2.6-km elevated stretch, costing ₹416 crore, will include Junpat and Boraki stations, expected to be ready in three years. The extension aims to connect to a multi-modal transport hub, integrating rail, bus, and rapid rail services.

news.title: ED probes high-rise clearance scam, seizes cash linked to suspended HMDA official
news.para: Enforcement Directorate investigates Siva Balakrishna, suspended HMDA director. Searches reveal suspicious real estate deals and unaccounted cash. The probe links to alleged illegal gratification for project clearances. Raids on realtors uncover incriminating documents.
